Rating: 4
Quick recipe to make from items already in the house! Unfortunately, all I had was yellow onions so I sauteed them just under carmelized and added the black beans to the pan with some cumin and a pinch if taco seasoning. This caused some beans to open which gave it a chunky refried bean conistency. (yay!) In a separate pan I quick sauteed corn w/salt & pepper & then mixed them both together. I used a little less cheese then recommended & served with mashed avocado on the side. A great finger food that my kids LOVED and asked for it to become a regular.

Rating: 3
I've been making this dish for years with absolutely no substitutions or changes. It's a winner in my family!

Rating: 4
Brought these to a friend's house for a new years eve party and they were devoured in 10 minutes! Changes to the recipe: a) Substituted scallions for the red onions as some of the other posts suggested. b) Threw the beans in the blender along with enough water to mix properly, then cooked them with chili powder, garlic and cumin. I did this to help keep the assembled cakes stay together since it would be served as finger food. Next time: a) Put only half of the beans in the blender. This will still help to hold everything together but having some whole beans in there will give it a better texture. b) Add canned or fresh chopped chilis to give it a little more kick.

